⏮⏭ Art & Culture | From 29th March head to thepostalmuseum in #Farringdon for new exhibition #VoicesFromTheDeep. After SS Gairsoppa was torpedoed off the Irish coast in 1941, hundreds of letters were recovered alongside historic artefacts & 109 tonnes of silver bullion - estimated to be worth £40m. 😱 Watch our Instagram Story for more information and a link to book the General Admission & Exhibtions ticket. It’s a fascinating story. A truly unique exhibition. And a considerable find given the boat was found half a mile deeper than the Titanic! 🙌🏼😳 Enjoy. || #thisislondon #londonreviewed #postalmuseum #voicesofthedeep || 🎥 daveburt

#LondonUnited thoughts from atp8 ... “1 year ago, disaster struck on Westminster Bridge. Paramedics from St Tommies rushed to assist as did police from nearby. Tirelessly, the emergency services worked, but sadly 5 people lost their lives. Something life has taught me in the last 12 months, is that you never know when disaster will strike so you should never take life or people for granted. Tell your friends & family you love them, make time for them, take those family photos and cherish them, for one day it will be our time to leave so don’t have any regrets. 1 year on London city stands united...” 🙌🏼❤️🇬🇧 || #thisislondon

mayorofldn has launched #LondonUnited to remember 2017 attacks. 
The campaign, developed in consultation with the bereaved families, survivors, emergency services and local councils, will use the hashtag #LondonUnited.

The hashtag will be projected on to the Houses of Parliament, London Bridge, Finsbury Park Mosque and Parsons Green Tube station to mark the anniversaries of each attack. 
The period of remembrance began today with the first projection at #Westminster and a social media campaign encouraging people to share their #LondonUnited messages, which will be projected at City Hall as part of a digital ‘book of hope’. Get involved! ❤️ || #thisislondon #londonreviewed || 📸 nigelhowardmedia for evening.standard

Art Editor belleannee checking in just in time for a beautiful Friday to turn into a snowy weekend:  Your must-see this weekend is about photography:  The hayward.gallery at the #Southbank Center reopened in February with an exhibit by #AndreasGursky.  Gursky is a German photographer who takes humongous images that show our world as we truly live (lots of people, lots of colour, really interesting). He is also the world’s most expensive photographer with a photograph of the Rhine River selling for $4.3 MILLION. (Makes you really want to practice your photography skills doesn’t it?) exhibit is on until 22 April. || Rad photo by edbartlett 🤟🏼 || #thisislondon #londonreviewed

Celebrating the life of #StephenHawking with the evening.standard in pictures... Stephen has died at the age of 76, peacefully at his home in Cambridge. At 22 Prof Hawking was given only a few years to live after being diagnosed with motor neurone disease. The British scientist was famed for his work with black holes and relativity, and wrote several popular science books including A Brief History of Time. We absolutely loved #EddieRedmayne’s film and portrayal “The Theory Of Everything” - if you haven’t seen it, perhaps watch it as the world celebrates his life. #RIP ❤️ || #thisislondon #londonreviewed

daveburt here. A little history and culture for you... 34 Montagu Square pictured here was once rented by ringostarrmusic. paulmccartney recorded demo songs there and worked on thebeatles songs like #EleanorRigby. Later, the legend #JimiHendrix would live there, which is where he composed “The Wind Cries Mary”. After that #JohnLennon & #YokoOno rented it - a photograph of which featured on their #TwoVirgins album. Just a little slice of #Marylebone. Fascinating! ❤️🇬🇧 || #thisislondon #beatles #paulmccartney #ringostarr #londonreviewed || 📸 daveburt

Art Editor belleannee says... In 2001 the decision was made to make most UK art galleries and museums free to the public.  Within 10 years the visitor numbers doubled with nearly 18 million people visiting our arts institutions annually.  Today the UK has five of the top 20 most visited art museums in the world (more than any other country). Two of art editor belleannee’s museum survival tips are 1) Go as soon as the museum opens, that way you and the staff are all at your freshest and 2) Research the highlights in advance.  It is super rewarding when your visit to a museum becomes a bit of a scavenger hunt. || 📸 Great photo of the tate by megastupidblonde 💗 || #thisislondon #londonart #londonreviewed

Art & Culture || belleannee says... The problem with #hyperbole is that when you want to describe something that genuinely is awesome, incredible or stunning ... words fail you because you already used them to describe some shoes or your blind date because he bought your coffee for you on Wednesday. That’s how I felt today at the vamuseum. 😲 Through a series of mistakes, a long line, a wrong turn, asking someone a question, mistaking one photographer for another, I wound up in the Opera exhibit with two 8-year-olds a 3-year old. Here is where words fail me and so I’m just going to have to lay it out and trust you to trust me. 😉 The #OperaPassion exhibit was the best thing I’ve ever seen in a museum. There is an audio element that interlocks seamlessly with imagery, costumes, paintings and history and geography lessons to create an immersive, enlightening, and visually and aurally stunning experience. I left with tears in my eyes. I kid you not. 😭 If you have the energy for but one cultural enrichment this quarter (or this year) please go experience this. ❤ (PS the Opera exhibit has nothing to do with this Dale Chihuly sculpture other than both are to be found in the vamuseum. I just loooooove it!) || #ThisIsLondon #LondonArt

Art Editor belleannee here checking in on a wet and cold Wednesday. The Old Royal Naval College Chapel is only the beginning of the incredible story happening in this #Greenwich landmark.  Britain’s largest ceiling painting is currently under restoration and for a limited time you can book tickets to get up close and personal with the project.  Climb up 60ft and receive a guided tour and a few of the secrets left there for us 250 years ago when the ceiling was painted.  This is genuinely a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity. || 📸 Gorgeous photo by elensham 💗 || #thisislondon  #londonart #paintedhall

Art Editor belleannee says... Two weeks left to see German photographer, Thomas Ruff’s exhibit at whitechapelgallery. Ruff has 40 years of photography on display - moving from analog to digital and walking us all through the what he has experienced in his life from 1979 to 2017.  It is a large-format, incredible reminder of just how quickly the world moves and changes. And how fortunate we are to have artists like Ruff documenting it all. ❤ || 📸 All photos by londonlivingdoll ❤ || #thisislondon #londonart #LondonReviewed

Imad, daveburt & melissa.hemsley say YESSSS! CookForSyria Pop-Up Charity Cafe opens in 7dialslondon 10AM DAILY starting tomorrow!!! 🎄 Join our launch tomorrow morning 10am! daveburt has just spent an hour with the amazing sixth-form business students of #HarrisCityAcademy in #CrystalPalace! 🔥 If you are growing up in #London you are in the most extraordinary city on earth... so do something with your life! Don't slip into the rat-race. Place a high value on your happiness. Do something you LOVE. You don't need all the things the world says you need. Don't be a slave to material things. Life is a marathon, not a sprint. And if you're finding life hard... talk to someone. We all have problems. So don't sit in silence. ❤👊🏼 Thanks for having me Mr T. daveburt 👍👍 || #thisislondon

#LondonArt by belleannee... Great #doortrait of the William Morris Gallery by josephowen. Morris is mostly known for giving his name to specialty wallpapers (he was a ground breaking designer of them in the 1800s) but was also an accomplished author and designer of church interior.  He was a a complex character: Oxford educated from a wealthy family, a prominent socialist, and an accomplished artist in his lifetime.  He also believed deeply that art was something for everyone, not just the wealthy. || Open Wed-Sun 10am - 5pm. Free. || #thisislondon #LondonReviewed

#LondonArt || belleannee says... You’ve got 6 days left to see the Tate Modern’s exhibit #SoulOfANation: Art in the Age of Black Power and we’d recommend not waiting until the last minute. The exhibit explores the role of black artists in the United States over a 20-year period starting at the height of the American civil rights movement in 1963. The artists might be new to you but their works will leave their indelible mark. Go in search of Bobby Swale’s “Superman” painting and Lorraine O’ Grady's 35-year-old “Art is....” which bares an eerie resemblance to today’s fascination with Instagram photos (they are actually outtakes from a performance art piece that encouraged onlookers - primarily people of color - to consider themselves works of art while also challenging the colour bias in the Art world). Lastly don’t miss Dana Chandler’s “Fred Hampton’s Door” the haunting ode to the murder of a sleeping black man by police officers in 1969.  It is a heavy exhibit, but it is well curated, timely and important.  It makes you think, a lot. And isn’t that what art is all about? || 📸 daveburt || #thisislondon #londonreviewed

#ThisIsLondon PART 2 | Stop what you're doing and WATCH THIS. Short film by Josh.Perrett entitled "New Beginnings". LINK IN BIO to watch full film. 🔥 We asked Josh to create this piece for a conference held by #MicroFocus in September which was called #DiscoverTheNew. 
When you think of discovery and new beginnings, or fresh starts, it evokes all sorts of feelings and emotions, and makes you look harder at the world around you. Josh has explored sunrises and sunsets, and uniquely captures the people and a perspective on London which makes this short, arguably the best piece of #London video we've ever featured. 
Thanks to Josh for his dedication and his relentless pursuit to capture so many exquisite London details. This is genuinely a masterpiece. Please share it with your friends and families. ❤️ DB

Proud to announce nextgenlondon & migrateofficial have combined for a fantastic book & photography exhibition called 'MIGRATE' themed around human migration. It also examines the point of photography & video in the refugee crisis: The exhibition - at #Omeara in #LondonBridge - is open now until 2ND SEPT. Pictured is example work from one of the 8 photographers from the exhibition... 📸 aliceaedy met Ashaluul, pictured here with her son, on a London bus. Struck by her beauty, Alice asked to make a portrait of her. She later learnt that Ashaluul, nicknamed Ash, is originally from Somaliland and as a child moved all over Europe, from Yugoslavia to the Netherlands. According to Alice, "She's now happy and settled, living in London as a single mother with her son... Ash says she feels more British than anything else".
DONATE on the door. Buy the book via link in bio. All proceeds will benefit Unicef's Children of Syria Emergency Appeal. 🌍💙 Please follow migrateofficial for more info.
#MigrateProject #AliceAedy #londonreviewed

#SomersetHouse plays host to the Sony WorldPhotoOrg exhibition with #MartinParr until 7th May. Our Instagram community had an exclusive preview Friday morning and the photos blew us away. Instagram can give us instagratification as we scroll through our feeds. I worry we don't take enough time to look at photos, and to understand the back stories. What is required to take a truly incredible photo? Patience. Sacrifice. Pain. Tears. Innovation. Discomfort. Risk. Love. Humour. It's all on display and you should make a point of getting down there, and take time to soak it all in. What a privilege. || 📸 daveburt || #londonreviewed #thisislondon #SWPA sonyalpha

Time for the launch of The Sony World Photography Awards & Martin Parr Exhibition at Somerset House - a complete celebration of photography for London. The exhibition is open 21st April - 7th May and will showcase the winning, shortlisted and commended images from the world's leading photography competition. It will also present a unique selection of images, books and film from legendary photographer #MartinParr. Get your tickets now. ❤ || 📸 mattspracklen || #thisislondon sonyalpha worldphotoorg #SWPA

'The 20th Anniversary Luminescence' by londonviewpoints feat. pli.panda sat down, as they take in the wonder of the Old Royal Naval College in #Greenwich. 💙 Inscribed by UNESCO as a World Heritage Site in 1997, the importance of Maritime Greenwich lies in its royal origins, especially under the British Tudor and Stuart dynasties, and its development from the 17th century as a site of astronomical research related to navigation, and of Royal Naval welfare and education. Make sure you visit. 💙 || #thisislondon #londonreviewed

#ESLondon & evening.standard Competition Winner: congratulations to 6stops for this fascinating photo, taken in #BankStation. Luke, joined by friends humannurture stee_v & lifeofteej convinced all the Londoners in the station, in the middle of rush-hour, to pose for this one photo. As you stare into the image you find all races, creeds and religions represented, Luke explains. 💗 Wishing everyone strength for today, and hope for tomorrow. 🎈Join us on Saturday 25th - 11.00 @ Battersea Power Station, as we mobilise the Instagram community onto the streets of London, to do acts of kindness all over the city. It's part of the instagram #WWIM15 initiative announced weeks ago. It just happens that kindness day is Sat 25th March - 3 days after the #WestminsterBridge attack. But we will use this day for good, and are taking more than 300 instagramers around London in a heart shaped route, carrying out acts of kindness as we go, and sharing the inspiration on Instagram. If you want to stand with us, you're more than welcome to join us. Sign up here for free: meetup.com/London-Instagram 💗 || 📸 findjoel feat. icreatelife_ 💗

❤ #LOVE can be our only response. 🙏🏼 Join us on Saturday. 11.00am @ Battersea Power Station. 300 of the Instagram community are gathering to love on London, and to carry out acts of kindness all over the city - inspired by our campaign dosomethingfornothing. Our route creates a heart over the city. We'll be releasing balloons as a symbol of love, hope and kindness. You can find all the info at: meetup.com/London-Instagram ❤ Bring yourself, your family, friends. Bring a willing heart and and let's do this together. Anger achieves nothing. Let's love our way through. ❤ || 📸 dimitarz || #DoSomethingForNothing #WWIM15

MUST READ: ClerkenwellBoyEC1 says.. A BRILLIANT night at the launch of imadssyriankitchen x CookForSyria pop-up 🙏🔥🍴🍖🍃 || Imad’s Story: Imad was a successful restauranteur in #Damascus with two restaurants, plus several juice bars
and cafes. But in the war, Imad's restaurants were destroyed, and he was forced to flee the
country in search of safety for his family. Making his way from #Lebanon through Europe, Imad shared his skills cooking for other refugees –
up to 400 at a time – and found even in the most challenging times, his passion for food and
bringing people together to celebrate life was strong.

When he arrived in the UK, Imad found work as a car salesman and was able to bring his family to
join him in England. He also became involved in our #CookForSyria initiative, helping raise money for Syrian children with Unicef's NEXTGeneration. Through this experience, Imad began to dream of running his own restaurant again. 
Launching 9th March, ‘Imad’s Syrian Kitchen’ pop-up restaurant on Columbia
Road will run until 24th March... tickets almost sold out - book quickly via imadssyriankitchen ❤

The menu will feature a series of beautiful Syrian dishes, which Imad has taken with him from Damascus to London.

The three-course set menu includes traditional dishes such as Fattoush (toasted flatbreads,
pomegranate molasses, tomato and cucumber), Kabsa (spicy chicken with cardamom and rice)
& Tabakh Rohoo (aubergine, squash & tamarind stew). Food has the power to bring people together from different backgrounds, races and cultures, and Imad’s Syrian Kitchen wants to do just that. This will be a family kitchen-table style supper, with food placed on sharing platters to be enjoyed with your fellow diners.

Through this pop-up, Imad hopes to start his new journey as a restaurant entrepreneur and make his dream to own a restaurant again happen. Imad's vision was made possible by the support of Unicef_UK@nextgenlondon laylayarjani appearherehq & hampsteadkitchn's Feeding Fund 🌿

Are you 18-25? If so. Listen. This is for you 💥👊🏼💥 #London is changing – do you want to be part of the revolution? Do you want to meet, listen and learn from world-class influencers at a special event? We're taking over the evening.standard Instagram for #YoungProgressMakers this Wednesday – an afternoon of discussions and debates around key skills and themes; entrepreneurialism, campaigning and technology. We also have 50 free tickets for young people from across London to attend the event. (LINK IN BIO). The event is for anyone who wants to make a change in the city. 👊🏼 It’s your chance to hear from the influencers of today – with on the day mentoring opportunities with london founder daveburt and others, and the chance to feed in your ideas for change in the capital. 🙌🏼. There will be dynamic talks, workshops and live performances with major influencers such as London mayor Sadiq Khan, Fabien Riggall of Secret Cinema, Baroness Joanna Shields and Good Chance Theatre. 👌🏼 As well as a host of thought-leaders and entrepreneurs there will be performances from Anita Barton Williams, Benna, Awate, Alula, Madi Maxwell-Libby and the Young People’s Laureate for London, Caleb Femi. (Free tickets via link in bio first come, first served). || 📸 mattspracklen

#CanaryWharf is to be lit up by 30 glowing artworks as the financial district showcases some of the world’s best illumination artists at its free #WinterLightsFestival. 🌀 Glowing angels, illuminated graffiti and floating lit-up poetry will all feature — and many of the works are interactive or responsive. London-born artist #MarcusLyall, who has worked on light shows for The Chemical Brothers, Metallica and Oasis, is showing his latest work, On Your Wavelength. Visitors put on an electroencephalogram (EEG) headset — which monitors brain activity — and are asked to focus on a thought which is then brought to life through 20,000 LEDs and music. || #LondonReviewed with the evening.standard || 📸 by NigelHowardMedia

Triple-Michelin chef dabizdiverxo & his team hit your senses and your palate; against a #Mayfair backdrop, a lively neon-lit restaurant with a wonderful open kitchen. Robata carabinero red prawns, crunchy pig's ear with strawberry hoisin, ali-oil and pickles, Galician octopus with tomatillo and green apple mole, just some of the entertaining dishes that came paired with over-sized cocktails like the Tokyo-Jerez cocktail. 📸 _zion_ || 'A Christmas Tree' by #ShirazehHoushiary at Tate ... The work, which focuses on the tree’s natural qualities such as texture, colour, smell and shape, hangs upside down from the glass ceiling in the Millbank entrance, its roots exposed and covered in gold leaf, drawing light and attention to what is usually underground.

Houshiary writes that she "would like us to contemplate that the pine tree is one of the oldest species and recognise the roots are the source of its continued stability, nourishment and longevity. As the roots remain hidden, it is best to seek what is hidden rather than what is apparent. As a Buddhist monk wrote, ‘An old pine tree preaches wisdom'..."

#LondonFood x CookForSyria || Our award winning Food Editor ClerkenwellBoyEC1 is launching the amazing #CookForSyria campaign today || CookForSyria is a new fundraising initiative with the goal of providing urgent humanitarian aid to children affected by the current crisis in #Syria || The initiative, in partnership with SerenaGuen founder of SUITCASEmag & NEXTGenLondon will kick off in London for the entire month of November with over 50 top restaurants cooking their signature dish but with a Syrian inspired twist with £2 from the sale of each dish going to Unicef_UK's Children of Syria Appeal || The campaign will then travel to other international cities including Hong Kong and New York || For those wanting to get involved, some delicious traditional recipes from Syrian families + modern Syrian inspired recipes top chefs and award winning cookbook authors will also be available on www.cookforsyria.com || The beautiful #CookForSyria non-profit Recipe Book is also now available to pre-order (link in our bio) with money raised going to children in need || Show you're support by spreading the word and by giving them a follow CookForSyria || #CommunityFirst #ThisIsLondon #CookForSyria 💕

Went to the #PaintedHall, Old Royal Naval College, #Greenwich... He  created this incredible image by stitching 5 photos together. The reflection is caused by a mirrored table in the room which is designed to help you see the amazing ceiling that took 19 years to paint. It was commissioned by Sir Christopher Wren & Nicholas Hawksmoor, and painted by Sir James Thornhill (the guy who painted St. Paul's cathedral ceiling). // The hall is going to undergo renovations for the next 3 years starting at the end of September, so there's very little time left to see it without works going on! DoSomethingForNothing Update || In less than 6 months, over 100 MILLION people have been exposed to the #DoSomethingForNothing movement. What started in #London and the UK is now stretching to the 4 corners of the earth. People from all different ages and cultures are taking inspiration from the movement and bringing unconditional love to people in ever increasing new ways. It's incredible. 🙏🏼 Thank you to everyone who has been sharing the news articles on social, and also sharing their own stories on #DoSomethingForNothing. ❤️
. 
This is David, 53 years old. He approached JoshuaCoombes as he was packing his things up for the day, but Josh couldn't resist his warm smile and the chance to hear his story. David is #Ethiopian, born there before moving to Denmark when he was a teenager. After losing his job and not being able to support himself he decided to come to London for a new start, hoping to work and to eventually return home to re-build a life he left behind. Unfortunately things haven't been as easy as he thought here. After a few weeks in a hostel, homelessness was reality - 'I just want to work, I have been looking for something in a warehouse but no luck yet.' David speaks English well, along with Danish, Swedish and Oromo (Ethiopian dialect). He is certainly a man who seems to need a break. Josh enjoyed chatting to him as the sun shone down, and wished him well. He told him he'd keep an eye out for jobs etc, and in the meantime, he is now his hairdresser. #DoSomethingForNothing ❤️

DoSomethingForNothing || Paul, homeless, cleaned up, and loved. 💕 Paul cried the whole way through his haircut. We believe he was violently attacked hours before he bumped into us, because he threw himself on top of a 78 year old friend to protect him from a beating. He took it instead. 🙌🏼 His legs, hands and head were extremely sore and bruised from where he had been repeatedly hit with bottles. In this moment I believe Paul's willingness to defend a friend means he's probably out-classed most of us. 💕👌🏼 Profoundly moving. We can't fix everyone. But for the time we are with them we can listen, we can hear their story, we can love them, we can be bringers of compassion and dignity. 💕 Paul loved his haircut. It made him happy. We left him smiling. He's #TrafalgarSquare based. JoshuaCoombes is now his hairdresser. ✂️💕 || Share your own stories on #DoSomethingForNothing - you might not be able to cut hair, but you can use your time and your own skills to make a difference to one person 💕 || daveburt mattspracklen

🇫🇷❤️ Of course love can't bring people back. But what other response can there be? Love never gives up. Love cares for others more than self. Love doesn't want what it doesn't have. Love doesn't strut. Love doesn't have a big head. Love doesn't force itself on others. Love isn't me first. Love doesn't hold onto the past. Love looks for the best, never looks back and keeps going to the end. Love never dies. It can never fail. Love unifies. Love heals. Love comforts. In the end... THERE IS ONLY LOVE ✨💥❤️💥✨ DaveBurt || #DoSomethingForNothing

SamuelMChurchill is with the #ColdstreamGuards who made their way from #BuckinghamPalace to #HorseGuardsParade earlier, to bring about the pageantry and military pomp for the Queen's 90th Birthday Celebrations 🇬🇧❤️👑 || #thisislondon #queen

🎉🇬🇧👑 Today is a good day to be in #London! The #Queen's official 90th birthday will be marked at the Trooping the Colour parade in central London later. More than 1,600 soldiers will take part in the annual display of military pomp and pageantry on Horse Guards Parade. The Queen will then join other members of the Royal Family on the Buckingham Palace balcony for an RAF fly-past. A flotilla of historic boats will also take part in a procession on the River Thames and Royal gun salutes will be fired in several cities across the UK. Happy birthday Ma'am! 🎉🇬🇧👑 || 📷 spectrumvisuals 👌🏼 || #thisislondon #bigben #jaguar

#LondonFood || Last night a burger changed my life! 😍 Welcome to the world of FlatIronSteak. We stopped here in #DenmarkStreet impromptu and sat in silence, lost for words, shaking our heads, wondering what just happened. 😳 rontimehin and mattspracklen enjoyed flat irons medium rare, I took the flat iron burger. The flat iron is the only reason people come here and it's the centre of their menu. We could eat a bucket of their chips. It's amazing value and perfectly executed every time. Don't be surprised to find a queue out the door, and if you persevere, you'll realise why people queue for this. It's easily top 5 recommends. 😍❤️👌🏼 daveburt || #ThisIsLondon #GoNow #LondonReviewed #WhatAreYouWaitingFor 😂

The stunning #ShadThames & #ButlersWharf snapped by drapes213. Butler's Wharf was built between 1871-73 as a shipping wharf and warehouse complex, accommodating goods unloaded from ships using the port of London. It contained what was reputedly the largest tea warehouse in the world. During the 20th century, Butler's Wharf and other warehouses in the area fell into disuse. To this day, one of our favourite streets in #London 😍 || #ThisIsLondon

#ClinkStreet by daveburt 😍 Narrow, dark and cobbled. It's best known as the historic location of the notorious Clink Prison, giving rise to the slang phrase "in the clink" meaning you were in prison. #FASHIONFOCUS // This morning we were up early to meet Katie Harland, founder of Rogues_UK, born only 18 months ago out of a desire to find the perfect flat shoe. London is Katie's home and inspiration for the brand, and it's a special moment when Rogues are spotted pounding the streets of London. The press and fashion world are in love with them, and there's no doubt we'll be seeing them on the likes of ChungAlexa, the Queen of Flats - great jumping team! 😍 || #GoRogue #ThisIsLondon #LondonReviewed #CommunityFirst || 📷 RonTimehin

#VernalEquinox - the first day of #Spring, as beautifully captured by whatalexloves in #Chelsea 😍💗 || The word "Vernal" is derived from the Latin word for spring and it is one of two that occur every year - the other being the Autumnal Equinox in September. The two equinox mark the moment the Sun crosses the celestial equator - the imaginary line running through the centre of the globe - from south to north. || What happens on an equinox? In Latin it literally means "Equal night" (Equi means equal and nox means night) because it means there are roughly 12 hours of daylight and 12 hours of night everywhere in the world. || #FactForSunday #ThisIsLondon || 📷 whatalexloves

#LondonMusic || This is RegentSounds in #DenmarkStreet. This wall of guitars used to be where the recording studio was. In fact, it still has the original flooring. Right on this very spot, The #RollingStones recorded their first self-titled album. #BlackSabbath also recorded albums here and #JimiHendrix got close to a recording, but was thrown out for being too loud! 😂 Fascinating stories from regentsounds. If you're a musician and interested in the rich history of the street known as #TinPanAlley, you need to pay it a visit! ~ London Music Editor // MattSpracklen || #LondonReviewed #ThisIsLondon #Gretsch

#FashionFocus || #PhilipTreacy OBE || Today we were lucky enough to get an insight into the creative mind of the World's most famous milliner, PhilipTreacy, who was famously rocketed into the limelight by the late Isabella Blow who made him an overnight creative success story by featuring his hat in 1997 Dress Of The Year. Nearly 20 years later Philip has made hats for every designer worth knowing (including #AlexanderMcQueen, #Chanel and #Valentino) and for just about every Royal Family there is. 🙌 It is difficult to explain in words the magic of Philip and his creations, perhaps it's best to quote #GianniVersace who said "Give Philip a pin and he makes a sculpture. Give him a rose and he makes a poem." ☺️ A National Treasure who is undoubtedly the best milliner this World has ever, and will ever see. || 📷 Photography by Kiat_Photography || 💃 Modelled by our very own JoRenwick || #thisislondon

#LondonReviewed || #BurlingtonHouse is a building on #Piccadilly in #London. It was originally a private Palladian mansion, and was expanded in the mid-19th century after being purchased by the British government. The main building is at the northern end of the courtyard and houses the #RoyalAcademy. This venue is also used for temporary art exhibitions for the academy, so it's well worth passing through. 😍 daveburt || #thisislondon

Another amazing #LumiereLondon exhibit caught by tom_westford. It spans #OxfordCircus and it's called '1.8', by Janet Echelman. The #WePioneerLondon Instameet concluded at our secret location, TheTattershallCastle - a beautiful 900 capacity vessel on the #VictoriaEmbankment that hosted us for our evening social! 🙌 This boat is amazing! It's open to the public and serves a wicked fish and chips with the best mushy peas I've had in a while! The crowd were grateful for hot chocolates and coffees (& beer!) on arrival after a cold conclusion to an incredible day! Thanks to WePioneer for collaborating with us, for everyone who came out, and to all our leaders for serving! We can do exponentially more together than we can apart ☺️❤️ daveburt // #thisislondon #communityfirst #londonreviewed

An air raid siren sounded over #London to commemorate the 75th anniversary of the #Blitz. Volunteers took a convoy of #SecondWorldWar fire vehicles to #StPauls for a service of remembrance at the fire fighters' memorial as captured by sophie1791 🙏 The night of December 29-30, 1940, became known as the "Second Great Fire of London" after 24,000 high explosive bombs and 100,000 incendiary bombs were dropped on the city by the #Luftwaffe. The bombs started more than 1,500 fires which developed into a larger blaze which threatened St Paul's itself. But our #cathedral was saved thanks to the valiant efforts of firemen and volunteers.❤️ // #ThisIsLondon #lestweforget

#WellingtonArch at the bottom of #ParkLane. 😍 The last 48 hours has been interesting for me & our team. I write from the desert in #Rajasthan in #India. Internet connectivity is in short supply! 😂 Yesterday we were detained by the Air Force for flying our drone over Amber Fort in #Jaipur. Little did we know the adjacent hill was an Air Force base, and that there had been a terrorist threat a few days before, resulting in their security being raised to the highest level. What started as a pursuit for beautiful footage ended with us explaining ourselves to the commander of the Indian army and their intelligence division! 😁🙌 We were spared a jail cell and 6 hours later we were released. Today we're reflecting on a funny adventure and a story we'll never forget! ❤️ patrickgather christabelsjournal jadefarmiloe #friendsforlife 😂☺️

#COMPETITION | Thank you to everyone who has participated in the VolvoCarUK #VolvoLifePaint competition. We've seen some incredible entries via #LondonLifePaint and will be contacting the most inspiring entrants shortly to send them their prize. Every year, more than 19,000 cyclists are injured on the UK's roads. Together with VolvoCarUK we are supporting road safety by sending out 30 cans of LifePaint, a unique illuminating safety paint which is invisible by daylight, but in the dark reflects light in the same direction as the light source. Congratulations to those who are receiving one of 30 cans this coming week! If anyone else wants to get their hands on a can, head to one of the 75 participating dealers in the UK and stay safe on the road! ❤️ // #thisislondon

Day 3 of our partnership with HiltonHHonors and today we explore fine dining in London’s tallest building, the #Shard. It’s not hard to pull a crowd when you have this view. But don’t think that AquaShard takes it for granted. Their British menu relies on local produce served as classic dishes, always with a twist. Expect flair in the execution, surprises even, and don’t expect to be left hungry. Great portions, and a super-romantic spot for love birds. ❤️ #HiltonAtPlay // #ThisIsLondon #LondonReviewed

It's the second day of our HiltonHHonors partnership and a chance to explore life on #Bankside. Not, the South Bank, but Bankside, which sits primarily between Blackfriars Bridge and London Bridge. Chase bubbles with your children or try visiting historical attractions such as Southwark Cathedral, London Bridge Experience, or Shakespeare’s Globe exhibition. There are many small galleries, and of course Tate which is unmissable. Enjoy cafe’s or a pint of beer in the shadow of St Paul’s Cathedral. #HiltonAtPlay // #ThisIsLondon #LondonReviewed

Often the very beautiful Tower Bridge is referred to as "London Bridge". If you're guilty of this mistake, it's a cardinal sin in London! 😁 Spot the difference between the two bridges! This is #LondonBridge and it isn't so fancy. It is however a major bridge connecting the north and south banks, commuters pour over it every day, and it carries our beautiful red buses around the clock. daveburt // #thisislondon

Making my way along the #JubileeLine. This is #TubeLife 🙏 Let people off the train first. Let someone else have the seat. Smile. It won't hurt you! Let's #sharethelove London! ❤️ daveburt // #thisislondon

Our HiltonHHonors discovery begins in the secret world of St. Katharine's Dock, where you will stumble across award winning coffee shop WhiteMulberries - the independent serves rotating coffees from top roasting houses. Expect chocolate melts, beautiful breakfasts, and bake goods that will make you cry! There is no other setting in #London offering such quiet seclusion, against a backdrop of beautiful yachts and boats. Pair it with a WhiteMulberries #FlatWhite and you'll be winning at life! 🙌 #HiltonAtPlay // #thisislondon #londonreviewed #stkatharinesdock

Going up, or going down? Whether you're up, or down, everyday we have choices. Choices about how we see the world and those around us. To stick with the job we're in, or look for something new. To prefer the needs of others, or just look after yourself. To build up walls of protection, or to open up your heart and risk it all again. To forgive, or stay bitter. To be positive, or negative. To love, or not to love. They're all our choices and they all have vastly different outcomes. Choose a better outcome. It's a new week ahead. It's a great week for new beginnings. You can't change your past, so why dwell there? Build a better future. Share. Laugh. Live. Love. Come on #London! ❤️ daveburt // #thisislondon #sharethelove

Last night's #supermoon. This phenomenon occurs when the #Moon is in the closest part of its orbit to Earth, meaning it appears larger in the sky. The #eclipse caught here by tomas_sent which made the Moon appear red has been visible in North America, South America, West Africa and all over Western Europe. This phenomenon was last observed in 1982 and won't come again until 2033. Those that were dedicated enough to stay up, were truly rewarded! 🙌😳 // #thisislondon

Coffee time reflections... We've just reached the incredible milestone of 1.5 million followers! Wow! 🙌😳🎉 In the last month, another 100,000 of you have tuned in and joined our adventure as we seek to tell London's story, with our own unique perspective, one beautiful moment at a time. We are passionate about celebrating London. It's the most visited and most instagramed city in the world and it's adored universally. We're also passionate about London's creative community. Some of the images we feature come from some of the most talented creatives in London. And it's a privilege that we get to share their gifts with you also. So a big thank you from me... thanks to the community for all their contributions and for sharing their amazing photos with us. And thanks to all our followers for watching, liking and commenting! THANK YOU ❤️ daveburt // #Snapchat: Londongramer

Queen Elizabeth II, snapped here by shannon__ashton, becomes Britain's longest-reigning monarch later when she passes the record set by her great-great-grandmother Queen Victoria. #TheQueen, who is 89, will have reigned for 63 years and seven months - calculated at 23,226 days. // Look out for a number of celebrations taking place in the city today... On the #Thames, a flotilla of historic vessels, leisure cruisers and passenger boats will take part in a procession between #TowerBridge and the Houses of Parliament. The bridge will lift as a sign of respect and #HMSBelfast will sound a four-gun salute. The #BTTower in central London will scroll the message "long may she reign". // #thisislondon #queen #royalfamily 🇬🇧❤️

What to say about my time with the #Wraith? It's honestly the most astonishing drive of my life. I feel privileged to have had it. 🙌 RollsRoyceCars have thought of everything. Literally, everything. It's not a boisterous "look at me" car. No. Yet look at it you will, like everyone in Oxford Street and Regent Street. In fact wherever I drove it, people simply stopped and stared. 😳 It's outrageous. It's majestic. It's classy. It's altogether other-worldly. There's something about #CarsOfBritain, isn't there? daveburt 🇬🇧 // Photo by the amazing icreatelife_ ❤️ // #thisislondon #carsoflondon #rollsroyce

#NottingHill through the lens of sparrowflu 😍 Notting Hill is THE place to be tomorrow as the annual #NottingHillCarnival street party kicks off. Sunday is family day. Following the opening ceremony and children’s parade, there will be performances throughout the day on the World Music Stage and the London Calypso Tent among other stages. The finale will take place on Monday — showcasing over 60 bands, hundreds of dancers and performers plus scores of colourful costumes and floats. But Sunday’s opening ceremony will take place in the judging zone, next to Westbourne Park station, at 11am. So set your alarms and enjoy! ☺️❤️🎉 // #thisislondon #londonreviewed #london

Also for videos, they can be played the same way. Thankfully our grid remains a tidy array of little squares. That keeps the OCD in check. 😉 BUT! That does mean the pure days of vintage instamatic-inspired square format images has ended. Kind of. I guess you now have a choice what you post. SO! We want to know what you think!
